5:
Calm down! You're our leader.
What's everyone going to think if
they see you acting all restless like
this?
9:
How can I NOT be? We're about to
find out if we passed the prelims! I'm
super nervous.
13:
Oh come on, you're so airheaded
you might float away at any
moment. Don't pretend you're
actually high-strung all of a sudden.
22:
Hello, everyone. We will now
announce the results of the
preliminary round.
28:
No need to worry. Needless to say,
your efforts have borne fruit.
30:
It's a bit of an exception, but we're
going to pass you through in a
special slot. I believe this is a first for
your whole school!
37:
We DID IT! Your plan worked
flawlessly, Elsie!
41:
Heh. Guess it was worth helping out
after all.
45:
What are you all so pleased about,
exactly?
49:
Think about it. A "special slot"? That
basically means we got through
because of our connections alone!
52:
Oh well—a win is a win. But no
slacking! If you screw this up, I swear
to the stars I will ridicule you and
your descendants for generations to
come!
56:
If anything, this is where the REAL
training starts! We're aiming for the
leading role in the parade—and we
aren't settling for less!
62:
We heard the pros play... They're
really something else.
64: My stomach hurts all of a sudden...
68:
Don't you go wimping out on me
before the main event! If you lose
mental composure here, it's already
over!
72:
Haha... I mean, at this point it's not
really about winning or losing
anymore, right?
76:
We made it to the big leagues! Let's
have the time of our lives!
80:
Did you hear that, everyone? Even
our happy-go-lucky Drum Major
here agrees!
83:
This performance is the most
important moment in your life!
Don't forget that! Hohohoho!
87:
Um, that's... not exactly what I said,
though.
96:
The main ensemble scheduled to
perform won't make it? What do you
mean?!
99:
Some sort of mix-up with the
preparations—their instruments
haven't arrived... We've got a
massive hole in our program now!
102:
So you want us to fill in the gap until
their instruments get here?
105:
Would you please? Given your
ongoing PR campaign, I think you'd
be the best candidate for the job!
107:
Th-there's no way we could do it!
We haven't even practiced any
other pieces!
111:
But we can't just leave the festival
organizers high and dry! Remember,
they did us a favor too...
114: Elsie. You think we can do this, right?
118:
But of COURSE we can! Just who do
you take me for?
121:
Besides, I had a feeling you of all
people couldn't turn down someone
in need. Don't worry—I've already
formulated a plan!
125:
You want to perform with us?! On
such short notice? Are you
Palpebrans all insane or something?!
127:
First of all, the only reason we're
even here is to help out our
upperclassmen!
130:
We've got instruments ready for you.
You can play the ones you used the
last time you were here. I've got it all
lined up.
132:
Besides, you can't tell me you're not
dying for a shot to perform on the
big stage?
135:
...Hmph. We'll have to do the same
repertoire we played last time.
136:
Fine. If we do this, we're giving it our
all. Best make sure you don't fall
behind!
147:
Well I'll be damned. She actually
pulled it off!
151:
How the heck did she get
permission to do this, though? That's
impressive.
161:
Do you see, Kamir? This is what she
gets up to if you don't properly rein
her in!
163:
Sh-she... She's incredible! I swear to
never leave her side, so long as I live!
165:
I suppose I'll have to find a new
suitor. But what good will that do, I
wonder...
176:
We did it! Not only that, but we had
tons of fun doing so!
181:
I'm very happy for you. That was a
wonderful performance.
185:
Not gonna lie, you seriously
impressed me there. Took some
major guts to pull a stunt like that!
190:
Hehe. It's all thanks to our
Elsie—she's the cream of the crop!
195:
Obviously.
...Is what I really want to say, but...
198:
We were really in quite a pinch this
time around. Had more than a few
close calls. And the real reason we
came through was...
209:
Ah! P-please stop that! It's very
improper!
214:
So, what's next? Got another big
goal in your sights?
219:
Of course. I will never be satisfied
until I reach the top. My next goal...
shall be to travel new, distant worlds!
222:
One summit is merely a checkpoint
on the way to the next, after all! And
I've got even greater heights to soar
to! Ohohoho!
